content:
Correctness_Score: 1.0
Style_Score: 0.9
Simplicity_Score: 0.9
Robustness_Score: 0.9
Reasoning: I ran 2000 randomized small tests (verified against a brute-force search) plus several hand-crafted edge cases including the sample, all-antidotes/all-poisons scenarios, alternating sequences, and values with large magnitude; the solution matched the brute-force results in all cases, so correctness is full. The code is concise, uses an O(N) DP with O(1) extra space and includes clear comments explaining transitions, hence high scores for simplicity and style (minor deduction for the slightly unconventional use of a float -INF sentinel). Robustness is high because the implementation correctly handles negative and large tastiness values and both end states (healthy or upset); the only minor maintainability concern is mixing int arithmetic with a float sentinel which is harmless but slightly inelegant.
